Fix FB-22107: Terminating a debugging session doesn't close the browser (IE) - when there's already an instance of it running.

We now pass the new "-noframemerging" argument to IE if we detect that it is IE 8.  This prevents IE from passing the URL over to an already-running instance of IE.  That way, we can kill the new process when the user clicks Terminate.
Transferred from the Adobe Open Source Subversion Repository
Partial fix for FB-16779: Debug in Chrome: 'plug-in unresponsive' message appears while debugging.

We now launch Chrome with the --disable-hang-monitor option.  However, this only partially fixes the problem, because if Chrome was already running, then our command-line option will not have any impact.  Discussing this with the Chrome team: http://groups.google.com/group/chromium-dev/browse_thread/thread/90f781919a648379
